27/03/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- During a visit to Skopje Saturday (25 March), US Senator George Voinovich voiced his belief that reforms in Macedonia would be implemented in a timely fashion.
In talks with President Branko Crvenkovski, Voinovich reaffirmed his country's support for Macedonia;
Crvenkovski in turn stressed that Skopje views its ties with the United States as a strategic priority.
The officials also discussed Macedonia's parliamentary elections later this year, agreeing that conducting a democratic vote is a key to the country's progress in Euro-Atlantic integration.
(Macedonian Government Web site - 27/03/06)
